<p>make it simple to read all the users from a hypothetical REST endpoint '<a href="http://api.fake.com/users" rel="nofollow">http://api.fake.com/users</a>'.  The endpoint always returns a json list of variable length, but can return at most 100 users at a time.</p>  <p>Some limitations I have to consider are that All users cannot fit in memory, the endpoint call might not return 100 users even if you ask for 100 and The endpoint call might error.</p>  <p>I am new to python so this is what I have so far.</p>  <pre><code>import json, requsts  url="http://api.fake.com/users" users=requsts.get(url=url)  params = {users, }  resp = requsts.get(url=url, params=params) data = json.loads(resp.text) </code></pre>